S. African Minerals Department Lacks Managers, Ex-Spokesman Says

-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 
2011-02-24T04:58:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/s-african-minerals-department-lacks-managers-ex-spokesman-says.html
  South Africa ’s Department of Mineral
Resources has a “long and growing list of vacancies at senior
management level,” which contributed to inefficiency at the
ministry, Jeremy Michaels, the department’s former spokesman,
said.  Director General Sandile Nogxina is retiring while four of
the five deputy director general posts are vacant, Michaels
wrote in the Johannesburg-based Business Day newspaper today.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
